# Product and Category API

This project is a Spring Boot application with CRUD operations for **Categories** and **Products**.

## Endpoints

### Category Endpoints
- `GET /api/categories?page={page}` - Get all categories with pagination
- `POST /api/categories` - Create a new category
- `GET /api/categories/{id}` - Get category by ID
- `PUT /api/categories/{id}` - Update category by ID
- `DELETE /api/categories/{id}` - Delete category by ID

### Product Endpoints
- `GET /api/products?page={page}` - Get all products with pagination
- `POST /api/products` - Create a new product
- `GET /api/products/{id}` - Get product by ID
- `PUT /api/products/{id}` - Update product by ID
- `DELETE /api/products/{id}` - Delete product by ID

## Technologies Used
- Spring Boot
- Spring Data JPA
- MySQL/PostgreSQL (Database)
- RESTful APIs

## Setup

1. Clone the repository.
2. Set up the database configuration in `application.properties`.
3. Run the application using:
   ```bash or vs code 
   ./mvnw spring-boot:run
4. Run the url in the chrome -- http://localhost:8080/api/categories
